+```
+
+## How It Works
+
+1. Scans `source_dir` recursively for master calibration frames (XISF and FITS formats)
+2. Reads FITS headers to extract metadata (camera, temperature, gain, offset, exposure, date, filter)
+3. Determines frame type from `IMAGETYP` header (MASTER BIAS, MASTER DARK, MASTER FLAT)
+4. Builds destination paths organized by type and camera:
+   - `BIAS/{camera}/{filename}`
+   - `DARK/{camera}/{filename}`
+   - `FLAT/{camera}/{optic}/DATE_{date}/{filename}`
+5. Copies files to destination with metadata-rich filenames
+
+## Output Structure
+
+```
+dest_dir/
+├── BIAS/
+│   └── {camera}/
+│       └── masterBias_INSTRUME_{camera}_SET-TEMP_{temp}_GAIN_{gain}_OFFSET_{offset}_READOUTM_{mode}.xisf
+├── DARK/
+│   └── {camera}/
+│       └── masterDark_INSTRUME_{camera}_SET-TEMP_{temp}_GAIN_{gain}_OFFSET_{offset}_READOUTM_{mode}_EXPOSURE_{seconds}.xisf
+└── FLAT/
+    └── {camera}/
+        └── {optic}/
+            └── DATE_{date}/
+                └── masterFlat_INSTRUME_{camera}_SET-TEMP_{temp}_GAIN_{gain}_OFFSET_{offset}_READOUTM_{mode}_DATE-OBS_{date}_FILTER_{filter}.xisf
+```
